8 An Act relating to appropriations and budget;
reappropriating funds to the Department of Commerce;
9 providing reference; restating amount and purpose;
providing for certain adjustments under certain
10 conditions; providing for noncodification; and
declaring an emergency.
11
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
15 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
16 REAPPROPRIATION: The amount of Twenty Million Dollars
17 ($20,000,000.00) originally appropriated by Section 3 of Enrolled
18 House Bill No. 1019 of the 2nd Extraordinary Session of the 58th
19 Oklahoma Legislature, to the Oklahoma Department of Commerce from
20 the Progressing Rural Economic Prosperity Fund of the State Treasury
21 created by Section 256 of Title 62 of the Oklahoma Statutes, for the
22 purpose to construct needed facility upgrades, such as fairground
23 arena connectors, electrical infrastructure, and facilities
24 associated with livestock events at a location where statewide
ENGR. H. B. NO. 2744 Page 1
1 even ts commonly referred to as a "state fair" occurs in the central
2 region of the state, is hereby continued and reappropriated in the
3 current amount and for the original purpose, as adjusted for
4 transfer, less any amount that has been expended upon the effective
5 date of this act.
6 SECTION 2. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
7 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
8 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
9 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
10 Passed the House of Representatives the 12th day of March, 2025.
